                <h1>Fixing Windows Background Service Issues</h1>
                <p>When a Windows background service isn't running, it can lead to various issues, such as application failures or slow performance. To diagnose the problem, check the Service Manager for service status, ensure that the service is set to start automatically, and review logs for any error messages. Restarting or reinstalling the service may also help.</p>
